Information
------------------------------

The documentary details the experiences of several teenagers who were forcibly removed from their homes and sent to Escuela Caribe at their parents' behest. The film focuses on the plight of a Colorado high school student, David, sent to the school by his parents after he told them he was gay. The film also documents the experiences of two girls: Beth, who was sent to the school because of a &quot;debilitating anxiety disorder&quot;, and Tai, who was sent for behavioral problems resulting from childhood trauma.

